===Etymology 1===
{{PIE root|en|(s)ker}}
From {{inh|en|enm|sherte}}, {{m|enm|shurte}}, {{m|enm|schirte}}, from {{inh|en|ang|sċyrte||a short garment; skirt; kirtle}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*skurtijǭ}}. Cognate with {{cog|nl|schort}}, {{cog|de|Schürze||apron}}, {{cog|no|skjorte||shirt}}, {{cog|fo|skjúrta||shirt}}. {{m|en|skirt|Skirt}} is a parallel formation from Old Norse; which is a {{doublet|en|short|nocap=1}}, from the same ultimate source.

